
# API Documentation

## User Management Endpoints

### Get All Users
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users
Accept: application/json

### Get User by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Accept: application/json

### Create a New User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com"
}

---

## Customer Management Endpoints

### Create a New Customer
POST http://localhost:8080/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "1234567890"
}

### Get All Customers
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers
Accept: application/json

### Get Customer by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/1
Accept: application/json

---

## Account Management Endpoints

### Create an Account (Transaction or Deposit)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "accountType": "TRANSACTION", // or "DEPOSIT"
  "initialBalance": 1000.0
}

### Get All Accounts for a Customer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/accounts/customer/1
Accept: application/json

### Deposit Funds
POST http://localhost:8080/api/accounts/{accountId}/deposit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 500.0
}

### Transfer Funds to Another Payee
POST http://localhost:8080/api/accounts/transfer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountId": 101,
  "toAccountId": 102,
  "amount": 200.0
}

---

## Credit Card Management Endpoints

### Create a New Credit Card
POST http://localhost:8080/api/credit-cards
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "creditLimit": 5000.0
}

### Get All Credit Cards for a Customer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/credit-cards/customer/1
